{
  "doc_id": "37733",
  "text": "Zemel et al [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] studied the implication of the agouti protein on the regulation of [Ca 2+ ] i . Agouti stimulates Ca ++ influx and promotes energy storage in adipocytes by stimulating the expression and activity of fatty acid synthase, an enzyme involved in lipogenesis, and by inhibiting lipolysis in a Ca ++ -dependent rat model [CITATION_3] . This model is useful for the assessment of calcium regulation in adipocytes of rodents, but human studies are also needed to test these pathways.",
